    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1900-07-20T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1900-07-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="556"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d556">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Thiébaut</persName>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1900-07-20">
                            <hi rend="italic">July 20, 1900</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 338.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have the honor to acknowledge, with much
                    appreciation, the receipt of your note of the 17th instant, transmitting
                    extracts from the journals of the French Senate and Chamber of Deputies relative
                        <pb facs="0566" n="468" xml:id="pg_468"/> to the resolution, unanimously
                    passed by both those bodies, thanking the American people for the Lafayette
                    monument presented to France.</p>
                <p>It will give me great pleasure to forward copies of your note and of the
                    inclosures to the Senate and the House of Representatives when Congress next
                    convenes.</p>
                <p>Accept, sir, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">John Hay.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
